            ************************
            *** AirNet use cases ***
            ************************

******************************************************************************
Basic use cases
******************************************************************************


== toyExample/toyExample  ==

Example which allows http and icmp and deny all other traffic.



== toyExampleClick/toyExampleClick  ==

Example which redirects all granted traffic to a dataMachine (click).



******************************************************************************
Static use cases
******************************************************************************


== staticFiltering/staticFiltering  ==

Example which filters traffic based on the destination host,
the network and/or transport protocol and/or port number.




== staticParallelCatch/staticParallelCatch  ==

Example which involves 2 catch() instructions in parallel with the same
destination in the carry().
e.g.: ( catch() + catch() ) >> carry()




== staticTwoFabrics/twoFabrics  ==

Example which involves 2 Fabrics in the virtual topology.



******************************************************************************
Dynamic use cases (dynamic network control function-s is/are used here)
******************************************************************************


== statThreeEdges/statThreeEdges  ==

Example which collects statistics on layer 2 exchanges.



== checkDataCap/checkDataCap  ==

Example which regulates bandwith usage by hosts.



== dynAuthentication/dynAuth ==

Example which authenticates flows based on the IP source address of the first packet.



== dynDM/dynDM ==

Example which redirects non-trustworthy flows towards a dataMachine (click).



== dynLB/dynLB ==

Example which balances traffic between two web servers based on the IP source address.
